Giving five stars solely because of whoever was working the counter at roughly 12:30 on 11/14. She was doing 50 things at once and somehow doing them well--a long line of customers and she was the sole cashier, phone orders between in-person orders, directing newer team members while doing all that, etc. I got my to-go order and didn't realize an item was missing. I had gotten maybe 50 paces out of the store before I heard "BRIAN!" and, on a freezing November day, out came that same person (in a t shirt) running up with my sandwich.  Sometimes you see people doing extraordinary things in very ordinary places. I don't know if this review will reach her or her bosses, but goodness gracious give her a raise and a promotion. On a very busy, very ordinary Thursday, they were working really hard and going above and beyond. Thanks for the great service!

I have been eating Z'Marik's yummy food for probably about ten years now!  I don't go super often, but when I do, I love the fresh seasonings and ingredients.  I used to order regular pasta, but now I order gluten free pasta.  They have many vegetarian options, and it's easy to go dairy free as well.  I pay $2 extra to add tofu to my pasta.  I wish it were just $1 extra for adding tofu to a small bowl.  Service is fast enough.  Cashiers aren't always the most friendly, but the servers always are.  It's easy to get a table during the summer, or for dinner during the school year, but more challenging to get a table for lunch during the school year (it's a popular place).  Parking in downtown Iowa City is a challenge, but there is street parking if you're lucky (with parking meters), or the first hour is free in the parking ramps.  Z'Mariks is in the heart of downtown, and there are many other things to do near the restaurant.

I hope 5 stars is equivalent here to 5 thumbs up.  The customer service here was superb today.  Had a very minor issue which was resolved with impressive speed and professionalism.  Very friendly staff made me very much want to return regularly.  Z marks the spot.

LOVE THIS PLACE. I've been coming here for years and I am never disappointed. All their options are wonderful, especially the regular mac! I always take friends from out of town here who have never heard of it and they too really enjoy it.

I ate here consistently from 2003-2007. I came back to town in  2009, 2013 and was shocked to remember the superiority of their food compared to chains like Noodles. To boot, I met the owners a decade ago and they're terrific people. My favorite dish is the Pesto Bowl.   You're missing out if you don't eat here and this is my first ever internet review of any establishment or service.

Eating at Z'marik's was one of the worst restaurant experiences that I have had in Iowa City.  First of all, the service is absolutely terrible, when I asked about one of the items, the cashier rudely told me to read the board. My colleagues and I had to wait almost 20 minutes for our food.Ridiculous! We could have gone to a much nicer restaurant had we known it would take this long. The spicy peanut was bland and the vegetables were no longer fresh. My colleague even found a hair in his food which is not surprising considering how the place did not seem to be very clean. The overall atmosphere was loud and rushed, and not a comfortable place to eat. DO NOT EAT HERE! I am definitely never coming back to Z'marik's again.
I love this place because you can get a decent sized meal (I recommend the Basil Mac N Cheese) without spending an arm and a leg.  Plus, their noodles are super tasty. ;-)
